# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MindGuide environment template
# Copy this file to `.env` and adjust values as needed.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Prisma SQLite database location.
# Relative paths resolve against the prisma/ directory (where schema.prisma
# lives), so `file:../db/custom.db` points at <project-root>/db/custom.db.
# The db/ directory is gitignored — safe for local development data.
DATABASE_URL="file:../db/custom.db"

# ── z-ai-web-dev-sdk ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The SDK reads its credentials from a config file managed by the z.ai CLI
# (`z-ai configure`). No environment variable is required for local
# development inside the z.ai sandbox.
#
# For self-hosted deployments you must provision the SDK config out-of-band.
# See: https://github.com/z-ai-web-dev/z-ai-web-dev-sdk for details.
#
# ZAI_API_KEY=""        # only needed for non-sandbox deployments
# ZAI_API_BASE=""       # override the default endpoint

# ── Optional: Next.js runtime knobs ───────────────────────────────────────
# Comma-separated list of origins allowed to hit the dev server (Next 16
# cross-origin guard). Production deployments should set this explicitly.
# ALLOWED_DEV_ORIGINS="127.0.0.1,localhost"
